condition.narrative: Not later than five months after the Signature Date, the Recipient, through the MOA, shall establish, and thereafter maintainthroughout the implementation of the Project, a Steering Committee to be in charge of the strategic guidance and general approvalof Project implementation activities, with terms of reference satisfactory to the Association (Financing Agreement, Schedule 2,Section I.A.3).

The Recipient, through the MOA, shall ensure that all the bidding documents and contracts include the obligation of the relevantcontractors and subcontractors to adopt and implement measures to assess and manage the risks and impacts of labor influx, workers?camps and child labor (Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.D.3).

The Recipient, through the MOA, shall ensure that the Project is carried out with due regard to appropriate health, safety,social,and environmental practices and standards, and in accordance with the Safeguards Instruments (Financing Agreement, Schedule2, Section I.D.1, including point b and c).

The recipient shall recruit an External Auditor with qualifications and experience satisfactory for the Bank no later than five(5)months after effectiveness (Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.A.5)

The recipient shall recruit an Internal Auditor with qualifications and experience satisfactory for the Bank no later than three(3) months after effectiveness (Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I.A.4)
